<!DOCTYPE html>
    <html lang="en">
    <head>
      <meta charset="UTF-8">
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
      <title>Codebase Architecture Review - jdmqademo</title>
      <!-- Tailwind CSS -->
      <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
      <!-- Mermaid JS -->
      <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid/dist/mermaid.min.js"></script>
      <script>
        mermaid.initialize({ startOnLoad: true, theme: 'neutral' });
      </script>
    </head>
    <body class="bg-gray-50 text-gray-900 font-sans leading-normal tracking-normal">
    
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
        <header class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6 mb-8">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Codebase Architecture Review</h1>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">Targeting Deep Modules, Seam Discipline, and Parallel Testability</p>
        </header>
    
        <!-- Top Recommendation Alert -->
        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-10 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-2">⭐ Top Recommendation</h2>
          <p class="text-blue-800">
            We recommend tackling **Candidate 1: Multi-Tenant State Isolation Seam** first. 
            Resolving parallel test execution flakiness provides immediate leverage by reducing the test run time from 1.7 minutes to under 15 seconds, and enables
  safe CI verification without disabling browser concurrency.
          </p>
        </div>
    
        <!-- Candidates Grid -->
        <div class="space-y-12">
    
          <!-- Candidate 1 -->
          <section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 p-8">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
              <div>
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-semibold px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">Strong Recommendation</span>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-2 text-gray-900">Candidate 1: Multi-Tenant State Isolation Seam</h3>
              </div>
            </div>
    
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs">Files Involved</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li><code>server/server.ts</code> (Backend server)</li>
                  <li><code>e2e/src/fixtures/test-fixtures.ts</code> (Playwright test client setup)</li>
                </ul>
    
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs mt-6">Problem</h4>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  The backend uses a single global in-memory database array. Tests executing in parallel across chromium, firefox, and webkit modify the same tasks
  array, causing statistics and task filter assertions to fail with race conditions.
                </p>
    
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs mt-6">Solution</h4>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Deepen the memory store by wrapping it in an adapter that uses a <code>session-id</code> header to route read/write operations to isolated, thread-
  safe dynamic stores. The Playwright fixture generates a unique session ID per test thread.
                </p>
    
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs mt-6">Benefits</h4>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Provides complete **locality** of test state. The interface remains simple (just an HTTP header injection), but enables massive **leverage**—enabling
  100% stable parallel test runs across all browsers.
                </p>
              </div>
    
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-100 flex flex-col justify-between">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs mb-4">State Flow Architecture</h4>
                
                <div class="mermaid">
                  graph TD
                    subgraph Before (Shared Collision)
                      T1[Test Worker 1] -->|POST /tasks| GlobalStore[Single In-Memory DB]
                      T2[Test Worker 2] -->|GET /tasks| GlobalStore
                    end
                    
                    subgraph After (Isolated Tenants)
                      W1[Test Worker 1: Session A] -->|Header: Session A| Router[State Seam Router]
                      W2[Test Worker 2: Session B] -->|Header: Session B| Router
                      Router -->|Map to| StoreA[(DB Partition A)]
                      Router -->|Map to| StoreB[(DB Partition B)]
                    end
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Candidate 2 -->
          <section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 p-8">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
              <div>
                <span class="bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 text-xs font-semibold px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">Worth Exploring</span>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-2 text-gray-900">Candidate 2: Deep Page Modules for Navigation and State</h3>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs">Files Involved</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li><code>e2e/src/pages/tasks-page.ts</code></li>
                  <li><code>e2e/src/pages/dashboard-page.ts</code></li>
                  <li><code>e2e/src/specs/tasks/task-management.spec.ts</code></li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs mt-6">Problem</h4>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  E2E tests manually navigate via raw URLs, manipulate responsive menus (like the mobile toggle button), and perform direct assertions on CSS classes.
  When layout structures shift (e.g. mobile vs desktop responsive views), tests break because Page Objects are shallow wrappers.
                </p>

                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs mt-6">Solution</h4>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Extend the Page Object Interface to internally abstract the viewport sizing. Methods like <code>navigateToTasks()</code> will automatically detect if
  the mobile toggle button is visible, click to expand it if necessary, and handle timeouts internally.
                </p>

                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs mt-6">Benefits</h4>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Spec files only concern themselves with domain behavior (creating, completing, and filtering tasks) rather than viewport layout concerns. Deletion or
  refactoring of layout classes will only require updating the page object implementation, preserving test suite stability.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-100 flex flex-col justify-between">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider text-xs mb-4">Module Seam Architecture</h4>
                
                <div class="mermaid">
                  graph TD
                    subgraph Shallow Page Objects
                      Spec[Test Spec] -->|click toggle menu| Page[Page Object]
                      Spec -->|wait for selector| Page
                      Spec -->|assert button class| Page
                    end
                    
                    subgraph Deep Page Objects
                      SpecDeep[Test Spec] -->|tasksPage.filterCompleted| PageDeep[Page Object Module]
                      PageDeep -->|Internal: Detect Viewport| Logic[Responsive Menu Handler]
                      PageDeep -->|Internal: Wait Predicate| Verify[Completion Class Matcher]
                    end
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

        </div>
      </div>

    </body>
    </html>

